1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:14,367
<i>I've noticed Emma has been more
irritable these past few days.</i>

2
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:15,400
<i>Maybe she's just in a bad mood.</i>

3
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:17,933
<i> I hope that's the only reason.</i>

4
00:00:18,067 --> 00:00:19,667
<i> Not something worse.</i>

5
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,300
<i>You don't have to worry
about me.</i>

6
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:22,333
<i> I'm okay.</i>

7
00:00:22,467 --> 00:00:24,367
<i>But what you did to our daughter
isn't okay.</i>

8
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:26,267
<i>She's been going through
a tough time,</i>

9
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:27,533
<i>and you've made it worse
by hurting her.</i>

10
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:29,767
<i>That wouldn't happen if Jade
stayed out of it.</i>

11
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:32,500
<i>Let's push your paranoia
to the limit.</i>

12
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:34,600
<i> Who's the crazy one?</i>

13
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:35,633
<i> It's you!</i>

14
00:00:35,767 --> 00:00:36,600
<i> Why are you still alive?</i>

15
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:38,100
<i> Emma, it's me, Jade.</i>

16
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:39,467
<i> I will kill you.</i>

17
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,233
<i>- Ms. Emma!
- Mom!</i>

18
00:00:42,367 --> 00:00:43,200
<i> Mookie!</i>

19
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,000
<i>Emma, why did you hurt your
child?</i>

20
00:00:45,133 --> 00:00:47,233
<i> What did I do?</i>

21
00:00:47,367 --> 00:00:49,333
<i>I can't understand what I feel.</i>

22
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:52,067
<i>I need to go back to my family.</i>

23
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,467
<i> Danilo, Mookie.</i>

24
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:37,000
Will they suture my wound?

25
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:41,033
Stop crying, dear.

26
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,167
You can do it.

27
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:44,233
You can do it.

28
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:50,233
Mom taught me to be brave.

29
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:56,633
And yet she's still hurt you,
baby girl.

30
00:02:01,967 --> 00:02:02,733
Dad...

31
00:02:06,367 --> 00:02:09,500
Dad, what's going on with Mom?

32
00:02:09,633 --> 00:02:11,800
Did I do something wrong?

33
00:02:11,933 --> 00:02:14,400
Or is there something
I didn't do?

34
00:02:14,567 --> 00:02:18,267
Dear, don't blame yourself.
You didn't do anything wrong.

35
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:26,100
Mookie, Danilo, I'll leave you
for now.

36
00:02:26,233 --> 00:02:28,300
I'll call the pharmacy's
security agency

37
00:02:28,433 --> 00:02:30,600
so they can look for Emma.

38
00:02:32,067 --> 00:02:34,533
Why? Where's Mom?

39
00:02:34,667 --> 00:02:36,233
Don't worry, baby girl.

40
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:39,700
I will do everything
to find your mother.

41
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,167
I promise you that.

42
00:04:03,433 --> 00:04:06,733
<i>I won't lose you again,
my child.</i>

43
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:26,933
Thank you, Nurse.

44
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,067
Dad.

45
00:04:29,933 --> 00:04:33,033
I wonder what happened to Mom.

46
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:35,933
I'm worried that something bad
might have happened to her.

47
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:38,100
Dear.

48
00:04:39,967 --> 00:04:43,400
Your mom is brave and strong
like you.

49
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:47,600
So let's trust that she's okay.

50
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,700
Mookie.

51
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:52,367
Jade.

52
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,467
Danilo.

53
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,400
I'm so sorry.

54
00:04:57,567 --> 00:04:58,533
Sorry for what?

55
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:03,933
I feel that it's all my fault.

56
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:09,800
Maybe I should've gotten
Emma checked

57
00:05:09,933 --> 00:05:13,033
when I noticed she's acting
strange.

58
00:05:14,767 --> 00:05:16,433
What do you mean?

59
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:21,300
Obviously, Emma is not in her
right mind.

60
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:23,933
She's gone insane.

61
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:26,867
I'm just very lucky
that I survived.

62
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,267
But you, Mookie.

63
00:05:29,867 --> 00:05:31,600
She hurt you, too.

64
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:37,967
I can't forgive myself if
I let Emma's condition worsen.

65
00:05:39,267 --> 00:05:41,500
We need to do something.

66
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:45,633
What are you suggesting, Auntie?

67
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:51,533
We should get Emma confined
in a private psychiatric clinic

68
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:53,533
once we find her.

69
00:06:17,533 --> 00:06:20,000
Emma doesn't know
what she's doing.

70
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:22,233
She almost killed me.

71
00:06:23,933 --> 00:06:25,333
She also hurt Mookie.

72
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,567
Wait. Hold on.
I can't...

73
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:34,467
I can't decide about
that right now, Jade.

74
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,767
I know, Danilo.

75
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:41,233
But we need to decide
what's best for Emma.

76
00:06:42,067 --> 00:06:44,900
Are we going to wait for her
to do something worse?

77
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:47,367
What if she hurt other people?

78
00:06:48,167 --> 00:06:50,533
She's even a danger to herself.

79
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:55,100
Maybe Mom can have a therapy
session at home.

80
00:06:55,867 --> 00:06:57,400
She can manage that.

81
00:06:57,533 --> 00:06:59,700
I promise.
Let's get Mom treated at home.

82
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:02,167
Mookie, baby girl.

83
00:07:03,467 --> 00:07:04,667
I know it hurts.

84
00:07:05,733 --> 00:07:07,867
But we have to face the reality.

85
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:12,233
Even I feel sad every time
I think about it,

86
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:16,867
but your mother has become
someone we don't know.

87
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:19,600
But, Auntie, I don't want to.

88
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:22,933
I don't want to get separated
from her.

89
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:28,533
Wait. Let's not talk about this
yet.

90
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:30,333
Let's look for Emma first.

91
00:07:33,567 --> 00:07:34,367
I'm sorry.

92
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:40,333
I'm so worried about my wife.

93
00:07:40,467 --> 00:07:42,167
It's okay, Danilo.

94
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,733
You don't have to apologize.

95
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:49,167
You have every reason
to be upset.

96
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:50,567
And don't worry.

97
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,500
I'll help you find Emma.

98
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:57,200
It's a promise.

99
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:41,833
I am Olive Caparas's sister.

100
00:08:45,667 --> 00:08:47,533
You mentioned it over the phone,
Ma'am.

101
00:08:47,667 --> 00:08:49,800
But you didn't tell me
your name.

102
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:52,200
You don't need to know.

103
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:56,033
There's something I want you
to do.

104
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,067
What is it, Ma'am?

105
00:09:02,067 --> 00:09:03,667
You need to find her.

106
00:09:08,733 --> 00:09:09,600
Her again?

107
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:16,567
I want you to scare her
once you find her.

108
00:09:17,733 --> 00:09:21,067
Make her paranoia worse
until she goes crazy.

109
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:25,133
So I can get even with what she
did to my sister.

110
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,767
The police almost caught me
the last time, Ma'am.

111
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:31,800
This will cost a lot.

112
00:09:31,933 --> 00:09:33,333
Don't worry.

113
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:35,167
I know your price.

114
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:38,700
Do you want me to bring her
to you alive?

115
00:09:41,867 --> 00:09:45,200
Don't ever hurt or kill her.

116
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:49,433
Just bring her to the place
that I will tell you.

117
00:09:50,633 --> 00:09:53,567
Make sure she's already insane.

118
00:09:56,033 --> 00:09:57,900
She must not recognize you.

119
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:06,400
And don't ever tell her
that I had her kidnapped.

120
00:10:06,567 --> 00:10:08,100
Understood?

121
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:09,267
Okay, Ma'am.

122
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,300
Good.

123
00:10:12,067 --> 00:10:13,167
Bye!

124
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:17,833
Hello, Jade.

125
00:10:17,967 --> 00:10:19,400
Can you come home?

126
00:10:19,533 --> 00:10:21,933
So that Mookie won't be alone
here.

127
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:25,433
I want to look for Emma.
I'm feeling restless.

128
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:28,667
Okay, okay.

129
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:29,467
Okay.

130
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,200
Mookie and I will wait for you.

131
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:33,533
Okay, Jade.

132
00:10:36,267 --> 00:10:38,133
Dad, any update?

133
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:40,067
Did they find Mom?

134
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,467
They still haven't found her,
Dear.

135
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:45,767
Is what Aunt Jade said true?

136
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:48,300
Does Mom already have
a mental problem?

137
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:53,633
What if Mommy Olive and Mom have
the same mental illness?

138
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:55,433
I know your mother.

139
00:10:55,567 --> 00:10:57,933
She's not violent.

140
00:10:58,067 --> 00:11:02,333
But I don't understand
why she became like that.

141
00:11:02,467 --> 00:11:05,033
This is the first time
it has happened to her.

142
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:11,100
Will you let her be in a
psychiatric clinic

143
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:13,200
once we find her?

144
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:19,967
If that will bring her back
to her old self, I will.

145
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:49,067
Where are you going?

146
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:56,567
Who are you?

147
00:11:57,367 --> 00:11:58,633
Don't you recognize me?

148
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:00,933
I'm the Reaper.

149
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:03,500
You're not funny.

150
00:12:04,867 --> 00:12:06,633
I'm not trying to be funny.

151
00:12:08,433 --> 00:12:09,700
I'm begging you.

152
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:12,433
Whoever you are, let me go.

153
00:12:12,567 --> 00:12:15,633
My family needs me.
I need to go back to my family.

154
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:18,233
Leave me alone.

155
00:12:22,767 --> 00:12:26,167
Oh, no!

156
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:28,600
Sorry.

157
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,133
Oh, no.

158
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:33,567
Baby girl!

159
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:34,833
Don't touch that!

160
00:12:34,967 --> 00:12:36,133
Okay.

161
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:38,433
- I'm sorry.
- Loida, please clean this up.

162
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:39,300
Yes, Ma'am.

163
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:40,967
I'm really sorry, Auntie Jade.

164
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:43,100
- It's okay.
- It slipped into my hand.

165
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:44,133
I'll clean it up.

166
00:12:44,267 --> 00:12:46,100
It's okay, Sweetie.
Everything's good.

167
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:47,667
Are you okay?

168
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,033
Why do you look so tense? Relax.

169
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,500
I worry about my mom.

170
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:57,300
She's been missing for hours.

171
00:12:58,367 --> 00:13:00,567
Do you have any updates
about her?

172
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:02,867
What did they say?
Did they find her?

173
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:07,267
The security agency hasn't given
an update yet.

174
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,900
But let them do their work,
Sweetie.

175
00:13:09,033 --> 00:13:10,667
Don't worry about it. Okay?

176
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,000
I'm sure she's fine.

177
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:14,933
What matters is for you
to eat and get some rest.

178
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:16,100
So you'll recover.

179
00:13:17,133 --> 00:13:20,200
I only want to know if Mom
is safe.

180
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,267
I know.

181
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:23,467
Me, too.

182
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:25,800
I've been worried sick all day,

183
00:13:25,933 --> 00:13:29,467
especially knowing that Emma
can't take care of herself.

184
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,667
Anyway, go on.

185
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,167
Eat this.

186
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:36,600
Stay in your room.

187
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:38,533
I'll have someone bring you
some juice.

188
00:13:39,567 --> 00:13:40,267
Okay.

189
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,300
Go on.

190
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:42,700
Go, baby girl.

191
00:13:47,067 --> 00:13:48,400
I'm begging you.

192
00:13:48,533 --> 00:13:50,900
Leave me alone.
What did I do to you?

193
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,933
Leave me alone!

194
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:55,533
I'm here to pick you up.

195
00:14:01,267 --> 00:14:02,400
Are you ready?

196
00:14:04,633 --> 00:14:06,167
Ouch! Crazy!

197
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:10,100
Wait.

198
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,067
Don't shoot.

199
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,267
I have a family.

200
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,033
Who are you?

201
00:14:17,167 --> 00:14:18,400
Take your mask off.

202
00:14:28,933 --> 00:14:29,567
<i> Mookie!</i>

203
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,100
<i> I told you to shut up!</i>

204
00:14:31,233 --> 00:14:34,133
You are Olive's henchman!

205
00:14:34,267 --> 00:14:35,300
Why are you here?

206
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:37,667
Why did you follow me?

207
00:14:39,133 --> 00:14:40,433
Who ordered you to do it?

208
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:44,867
<i> Olive?</i>

209
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,500
<i> Why are you still alive?</i>

210
00:14:46,633 --> 00:14:48,067
<i> I'll kill you!</i>

211
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,300
<i> Emma!</i>

212
00:14:49,433 --> 00:14:50,367
<i> Emma, stop!</i>

213
00:14:51,867 --> 00:14:53,033
<i>- Emma!
- Mookie!</i>

214
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:54,567
<i>Emma, why did you hurt your
daughter?</i>

215
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:55,867
<i> What have you done?</i>

216
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,333
Is Jade the one behind this?

217
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,067
Is it her?

218
00:15:01,367 --> 00:15:02,333
Jade will kill me.

219
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,167
Jade will kill me.

220
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:06,133
I'm not crazy.
I was right all along.

221
00:15:06,267 --> 00:15:07,333
Jade will kill me.

222
00:15:07,467 --> 00:15:10,400
Mookie and Danilo should know
about it.

223
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:11,567
She will kill me.

224
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:12,867
I'm not crazy.

225
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:18,000
I was right. She will kill me.
I should tell Danilo and Mookie.

226
00:15:18,133 --> 00:15:19,267
I must go back to them.

227
00:15:20,633 --> 00:15:21,900
I'll go back to them.

228
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:26,833
Mookie!

229
00:15:30,633 --> 00:15:34,033
I told you that she shouldn't
recognize you.

230
00:15:34,167 --> 00:15:36,800
You were so dumb
for a gun owner!

231
00:15:37,733 --> 00:15:38,867
You're useless.

232
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:44,200
<i> Emma will come here for sure.</i>

233
00:15:53,267 --> 00:15:54,133
Hello.

234
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:57,500
We'll proceed with the plan.

235
00:15:57,633 --> 00:15:59,200
Come here as fast as you can.

236
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:02,400
You know what to do.

237
00:16:05,267 --> 00:16:07,900
There's still no news
about Emma.

238
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:10,800
Auntie Jade, is there no one
we can ask for help from?

239
00:16:10,933 --> 00:16:12,433
To look for Mom?

240
00:16:15,667 --> 00:16:19,100
I know we agreed not to report
it to the police.

241
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:22,467
But I now want to ask them
for help.

242
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,733
Me too, Danilo.

243
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:26,567
But Emma isn't considered
a missing person yet.

244
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:29,533
She hasn't been missing
for 48 hours.

245
00:16:29,667 --> 00:16:35,333
I can't just stand here
while my wife is missing.

246
00:16:35,467 --> 00:16:38,267
You're here for Mookie, Danilo.

247
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,800
Your daughter needs you, too.

248
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:44,767
And I know we still haven't
finalized it yet.

249
00:16:44,933 --> 00:16:49,233
But I've already called
the medical team

250
00:16:49,367 --> 00:16:51,067
of the mental health clinic.

251
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,933
What for, Auntie Jade?

252
00:16:53,067 --> 00:16:56,167
They need to talk to us about
your mom.

253
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:57,867
They have a pre-assessment
interview

254
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,933
regarding Emma's mental health
condition.

255
00:17:03,233 --> 00:17:04,233
Mookie!

256
00:17:05,067 --> 00:17:05,567
Mom?

257
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:06,800
- Danilo!
- Emma!

258
00:17:06,933 --> 00:17:08,567
- That's Mom!
- Loida, is that Emma?

259
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,133
Mom!

260
00:17:10,267 --> 00:17:11,700
Emma!

261
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:12,467
Mookie!

262
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:13,133
Mom!

263
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:13,833
Emma!

264
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,600
- Mom!
- Where have you been?

265
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:17,833
What happened to you?

266
00:17:17,967 --> 00:17:20,567
Emma, I was so worried
about you.

267
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:23,300
We've been waiting for you,
Emma!

268
00:17:23,433 --> 00:17:26,100
I'm glad my prayers have been
answered!

269
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:27,633
You're home!

270
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:34,100
I can now execute my plans
against you, Emma.

271
00:17:34,233 --> 00:17:37,533
You're a poor mouse walking
into my trap.

272
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:39,567
Demon!

273
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:40,767
Emma!

274
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:41,667
Mom!

275
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:42,633
Why? What did...

276
00:17:42,767 --> 00:17:44,733
How dare you drag God into your
evilness!

277
00:17:44,867 --> 00:17:45,533
Mom?

278
00:17:45,667 --> 00:17:46,800
You're going to kill me.

279
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:48,033
She's going to kill me.

280
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,933
She almost killed me.

281
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:51,900
Emma, what are you talking
about?

282
00:17:52,033 --> 00:17:54,933
Danilo, she seems
to be paranoid.

283
00:17:55,067 --> 00:17:57,367
Stop denying it!

284
00:17:57,500 --> 00:18:00,300
You told Olive's henchman
to follow me to the woods!

285
00:18:00,433 --> 00:18:01,100
Let go of me!

286
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:02,600
-Mom!
-Emma!

287
00:18:02,733 --> 00:18:03,467
What are you saying?

288
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,267
Olive is dead.

289
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,467
Maybe you're just imagining
things that happened before.

290
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:08,900
But she's gone.

291
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:10,467
Danilo, believe me.

292
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:11,667
Believe me!

293
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:12,300
I saw it.

294
00:18:12,433 --> 00:18:14,333
I saw Olive's henchman.

295
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:15,167
I saw him.

296
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:16,467
Mookie.

297
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:18,467
He's the same man who abducted
us before.

298
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:22,167
He was wearing a scary mask.
He looked like an old man.

299
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:26,033
An old man! He was so scary.
You will kill me!

300
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:27,200
Mask?

301
00:18:27,333 --> 00:18:28,700
Abducted?

302
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:29,567
Emma.

303
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:31,667
Emma, what are you talking
about?

304
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:35,700
Danilo, look what's happening
to Emma!

305
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:37,967
She needs help!

306
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:44,033
- Emma!
- Mom!

307
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:45,200
I'll kill you!

308
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,067
Mom!

309
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:51,800
Emma, stop!

310
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:54,167
Jade didn't do anything wrong
to you!

311
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:56,833
She's actually so worried
about you!

312
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,700
She's just pretending.
She's fooling us!

313
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:01,167
She's fooling us!

314
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:04,800
- I'm not doing anything to you.
- Mom, what's happening to you?

315
00:19:04,933 --> 00:19:07,333
This is the second time you
hurt Aunt Jade.

316
00:19:07,467 --> 00:19:11,233
I didn't know you could do
such a thing!

317
00:19:11,367 --> 00:19:13,467
Mookie, believe me.

318
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,000
I'm telling the truth.

319
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:17,800
She's the bad one!

320
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:21,067
You're no longer the Mommy Emma
I knew.

321
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,967
What's happening to you, Mom?

322
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:26,033
Danilo, you need to make
a decision.

323
00:19:26,167 --> 00:19:27,500
Look at what's happening
to Emma.

324
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:31,167
- This is not right anymore.
- Dear, it's still me.

325
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:32,267
Shut up!

326
00:19:34,233 --> 00:19:36,100
Mookie, it's still me.

327
00:19:36,233 --> 00:19:37,100
Dear!

328
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:39,333
Hey, what's this?

329
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:40,267
I'm not sick!

330
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,000
Dan!

331
00:19:41,133 --> 00:19:41,967
Dan!

332
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:44,633
Emma, what we're going
to do is for you.

333
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:45,833
This is for you.

334
00:19:45,967 --> 00:19:48,233
Dan! What are you doing?

335
00:19:49,433 --> 00:19:52,967
I'm not crazy!
Don't let them do this!

336
00:19:53,100 --> 00:19:55,200
Mookie!

337
00:19:55,333 --> 00:19:59,800
- Mom! I'm sorry!
- Mookie!

338
00:20:00,867 --> 00:20:01,933
Mookie, it's still me!

339
00:20:02,633 --> 00:20:03,567
Dear!

340
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:05,233
Hey!

341
00:20:05,367 --> 00:20:08,433
What's this? I'm not sick! Dan!

342
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:10,933
Emma, what we're going to do
is for you.

343
00:20:11,067 --> 00:20:12,767
This is for you.

344
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:15,267
Dan! What are you doing?

345
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:19,867
I'm not crazy!
Don't let them do this!

346
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,600
Mookie!

347
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:25,167
Mom! I'm sorry, Mom!

348
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:27,100
- Sorry!
- Mookie!

349
00:20:27,233 --> 00:20:29,167
Don't hurt her!

350
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:34,400
<i> You're right, Emma.</i>

351
00:20:34,533 --> 00:20:36,100
<i> I'm a demon.</i>

352
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:38,333
<i> Welcome to hell.</i>

353
00:20:39,933 --> 00:20:41,600
Mookie!

354
00:20:41,733 --> 00:20:42,967
Danilo!

355
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:45,767
I don't want to come with you!

356
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:49,867
Mookie!
Mookie!

357
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:57,333
Danilo!

358
00:20:57,467 --> 00:20:58,567
I'm begging you.

359
00:20:58,700 --> 00:21:00,433
Mookie.

360
00:21:00,567 --> 00:21:02,167
Let go of me.

361
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,467
I don't want to come.

362
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,500
I don't want to! I'm not crazy!

363
00:21:05,633 --> 00:21:06,733
I'll follow Emma.

364
00:21:06,867 --> 00:21:07,600
Dad!

365
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:09,133
Dad, I'll go with you.

366
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:10,100
Please, Dad.

367
00:21:10,233 --> 00:21:12,000
- Let me go with you.
- Mookie, no.

368
00:21:12,133 --> 00:21:15,433
You'll only get hurt when you
see your mom's condition.

369
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:17,633
Dad, please.

370
00:21:17,767 --> 00:21:18,867
- Let me come with you.
- No, no.

371
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:19,400
We'll go instead.

372
00:21:19,533 --> 00:21:20,533
Mookie.

373
00:21:20,667 --> 00:21:22,467
I'll take care of your mom.

374
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:25,167
I won't neglect her.
I'll take care of her.

375
00:21:25,300 --> 00:21:27,967
I promise you that. Okay?

376
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:29,333
Auntie, please.

377
00:21:29,467 --> 00:21:32,533
Please, make sure my mom gets
better there.

378
00:21:32,667 --> 00:21:34,100
I will.

379
00:21:34,233 --> 00:21:35,833
I'll take care of your mother.

380
00:21:35,967 --> 00:21:37,133
Okay?

381
00:21:37,267 --> 00:21:38,900
Danilo, I'll change my clothes
first.

382
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:40,100
Okay, okay.

383
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:41,200
Mookie.

384
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:43,067
Stay here, dear.

385
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:44,267
Stay here.

386
00:21:57,833 --> 00:22:01,533
Let go of me!

387
00:22:01,667 --> 00:22:03,633
Mookie!

388
00:22:03,767 --> 00:22:05,467
Dan!

389
00:22:08,567 --> 00:22:10,767
I don't want it anymore.

390
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:16,500
She's so insane.

391
00:22:16,667 --> 00:22:18,567
They're demons. Kill them.

392
00:22:18,700 --> 00:22:19,833
They'll kill you.

393
00:22:19,967 --> 00:22:21,567
They're evil.

394
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:24,367
You need to take care
of yourself.

395
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:26,967
Don't forget that Mookie
needs you.

396
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:31,567
And I'm also here to help you.

397
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:33,700
It's time for your medication.

398
00:22:33,833 --> 00:22:35,533
I saw you and Jade!

399
00:22:35,667 --> 00:22:36,633
You're in cahoots!

400
00:22:36,767 --> 00:22:37,967
Don't!

401
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:39,800
You're mind is making that up.
That's why you need medicine.

402
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:45,133
I'm just thinking if we did the
right thing in putting Mom

403
00:22:45,267 --> 00:22:46,800
in a psychiatric clinic.

404
00:22:46,933 --> 00:22:47,800
Behave.

405
00:22:47,933 --> 00:22:49,167
Your family is here.

406
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:56,300
- Emma!
- Mom!

407
00:22:56,433 --> 00:22:58,100
They're planning something
evil against me.

408
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:00,433
Emma!

409
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:02,333
You're a monster!

410
00:23:02,467 --> 00:23:03,467
I will kill you!
